node.text:
Starting with the upcoming Summer Paralympics in Tokyo, Paralympic medalists will now earn the same pay as their Olympian counterparts. The change was originally announced shortly after the 2018 Winter Olympics & Paralympics in South Korea.

According to the NY Times, Paralympic payouts were $7,500, $5,250, and $3,750 for a gold, silver, and bronze, respectively. Now they will be given $37,500 for golds, $22,500 for silvers, and $15,000 for bronzes, per the IPC.

#paralympics #tokyoolympics #equality #worldnews

node.text:
U.S. Customs and Border Protection is terminating two border wall contracts in the Laredo, TX, area, according to a statement released on July 23 by the U.S. Department of Homeland Security. ⁠
⁠
The contracts would have funded the construction of approximately 31 miles of a border wall. Construction on the wall had not begun.⁠
⁠
‘The cancellation of these two contracts is a huge nail in the coffin for this entire misguided project,’ Tricia Cortez, executive director of Rio Grande International Study Center, said to the Houston Chronicle.⁠
⁠
#texas #mexico #border #wall #biden #potus #immigration #politics
